com.vmware.vcenter.trusted_infrastructure.trust_authority_clusters

Interface ConsumerPrincipals

  • All Superinterfaces:
    com.vmware.vapi.internal.bindings.CompletionStageService, ConsumerPrincipalsTypes, Service
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ConsumerPrincipalsStub

    public interface ConsumerPrincipals
extends Service, ConsumerPrincipalsTypes, com.vmware.vapi.internal.bindings.CompletionStageService
    The ConsumerPrincipals interface configures the token policies and STS trust necessary for the workload vCenter to query the trusted services for their status. This interface was added in vSphere API 7.0.0.0.

    • Method Detail

      • create

        ConsumerPrincipals.CreateInvocation create(java.lang.String cluster,
                                           ConsumerPrincipalsTypes.CreateSpec spec)
        Creates a profile with the specified connection information on all hosts from a Trust Authority Cluster. This method was added in vSphere API 7.0.0.0.

        Invocation Result:
        a unique identifier of the profile The return value will be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.esx.authentication.clientprofile.

        Operation Errors:
        AlreadyExists - if a profile for the issuer already exists.
        Error - if there is a generic error.
        NotFound - if there is no such cluster.
        Unauthenticated - if the user can not be authenticated.

        Parameters:
        cluster - The ID of the Trust Authority Cluster to configure. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: ClusterComputeResource.
        spec - The CreateSpec specifying the connection information.
        Returns:
        instance of ConsumerPrincipals.CreateInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described create operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.

      • delete

        ConsumerPrincipals.DeleteInvocation delete(java.lang.String cluster,
                                           java.lang.String profile)
        Removes the read-only policy configured on ESX for a specific principal. This method was added in vSphere API 7.0.0.0.

        Operation Errors:
        Error - if there is a generic error.
        NotFound - if there is no profile configured with that ID.
        Unauthenticated - if the user can not be authenticated.

        Parameters:
        cluster - The ID of the Trust Authority Cluster to configure. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: ClusterComputeResource.
        profile - The ID of the connection profile to modify. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.esx.authentication.clientprofile.
        Returns:
        instance of ConsumerPrincipals.DeleteInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described delete operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
